article.description: — Cameron Krutwig had 16 points as Loyola of Chicago beat Indiana State 58-48 on Monday night.
article.headline: Krutwig lifts Loyola of Chicago over Indiana State 58-48
article.linkText: Krutwig lifts Loyola of Chicago over Indiana State 58-48
article.story: TERRE HAUTE, Ind. -- — Cameron Krutwig had 16 points as Loyola of Chicago beat Indiana State 58-48 on Monday night. Krutwig was 7 of 11 from the field, and he also grabbed eight rebounds for Loyola (8-3, 3-1 Missouri Valley Conference). Jake LaRavia had 11 points for the Sycamores (4-7, 1-5). Tyreke Key added six rebounds. The Ramblers leveled the season series against the Sycamores. Indiana State defeated Loyola of Chicago 76-71 on Sunday. ------ For more AP college basketball coverage: https://apnews.com/Collegebasketball and http://twitter.com/AP--Top25 ------ This was generated by Automated Insights, http://www.automatedinsights.com/ap, using data from STATS LLC, https://www.stats.com
